Hi friends =F0=9F=91=8B,
Happy Monday! This is, uhh, an important week here in the United States. Wi=
th nearly 100 million early votes already in, tomorrow is officially Electi=
on Day. If you haven=E2=80=99t voted already, let this serve as one of hund=
reds of reminders you=E2=80=99ll get today across the internet: VOTE. Find =
the nearest polling place or early voting locations here:=20
Because it=E2=80=99s not a normal week, I=E2=80=99m not going to write a no=
rmal post today. I=E2=80=99ll keep it short(er) and sweet and highlight lea=
dership lessons from my favorite piece of writing: former Philadelphia 76er=
s GM Sam Hinkie=E2=80=99s Resignation Letter [https://email.mg2.substack.co=
m/c/eJxFUDuO7CAQPM0QWvzsxQHBJnsNhKE9RoPBguZZfqdfxhOs1OpSf0tVziI8c7n0kSuSVqG=
Y4DWbuBKjnInX0jM1KhKqWQvAbkPUWBqQoy0xOIshp_uCUj6STQvBOKzzZEEJ-zUqPnEJYnGzVX=
Ye5UrePMY2HyA50PAPypUTkKg3xKM-xPeD__Q4z3OAeqTB5b2Xh1975pRNHaikb0iLNVtIrwCmg=
LcOh75Fgua07zHKmRg5FwMbYmsg5X_M20PS_cmH2paK1r3ez0nRKeOSS0jPPn5tdod4D7pC03Fv=
KeBlINklgv-Ix49dtxa8DtAJzhoBEcqneXuohJypIp3N525c-iP6BSSTfos].
I=E2=80=99m a huge Sixers fan, so I=E2=80=99m biased, but I promise you don=
=E2=80=99t even need to know what basketball is to appreciate Sam Hinkie, T=
he Process, and the courage to do the hard thing in the face of ridicule. A=
s one former Sixers colleague told SI [https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJx=
FUMtuhDAM_BpyA-UBLBxy6KW_gRwwS7QhQYlTRL--WfZQyZqRbVkznhkInyFe-giJWE4YJ7to0c=
tBde3IFt0uYugGZtO0RsQdrNMUM7IjG2dnIBv8fcG57NimH2vPgY_AcTQSZG9WVEIM62M0veKSs=
7fOBHmx6GfU-IPxCh6Z0xvRkSr1VcnvUud5Nsk2c9hL4w0UlFz0hYQooHiBBHu9Wf-yWMNKGGva=
sD5imDGl-tisgwVdYagfPcbErJbFgRBcCtVJqRrRuJyxbX8pbFXL96dsUjaJYH69lVnUPpAJ0fp=
nWb822NHdi_L8VHjP3tI1oQfjcPnkQp8k7zfpOlB7PJNDKv4-wzveQbUjH1hRW0LJ1P8L_QGC2I=
ea], Hinkie=E2=80=99s approach =E2=80=9Ccould be applied to a draft or an a=
partment search or a dating website.=E2=80=9D
I=E2=80=99ve been wanting to write about the letter for a while, and this w=
eek is right for two reasons.=20
First, last week, the Sixers hired former Rockets GM, Daryl Morey, to becom=
e their President of Basketball Operations. Morey made waves last year when=
 he tweeted in solidarity with the Hong Kong protestors, but for our purpos=
es, what=E2=80=99s relevant is that Hinkie was Morey=E2=80=99s protege in H=
ouston before he joined the Sixers. As ESPN=E2=80=99s Pablo Torre put it, =
=E2=80=9CThe Philadelphia 76ers kind of just hired their ex-wife=E2=80=99s =
older sister.=E2=80=9D With Morey and new coach Doc Rivers, the post-Proces=
s era is officially over, and The Process is back!=20
Second, tomorrow, the United States is electing a (hopefully new) President=
=2E It=E2=80=99s a good time to reflect=20=
on what makes a good leader, and Hink=
ie=E2=80=99s stoicism and peaceful transition out of the Sixers organizatio=
n is an example that I hope Trump follows. Of course, I abhor Trump because=
 I think he=E2=80=99s morally bankrupt and is willing to destroy Democracy =
for personal gain. But even if you=E2=80=99re willing to accept his persona=
l flaws, he=E2=80=99s also an inexcusably short-term thinker, constantly tr=
ading what=E2=80=99s popular with his supporters today even for what=E2=80=
=99s in their best interest tomorrow. He=E2=80=99s the opposite of Sam Hink=
ie. No complex organization can survive a leader incapable of recognizing t=
he long-term implications of their actions, including the United States. Vo=
te.
