in: 0 0 1em 0;">When Sam Hinkie arrived in Philadelphia, the Sixers were th=
e worst thing an NBA team could be: mediocre. They finished the 2012-2013 N=
BA season with 34 wins and 48 losses. Even worse, the team had a barren ros=
ter and no hope. As Sam Hinkie told ownership, reflecting back three years =
later, &#8220;Your crops had been eaten.&#8221;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a=
1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">The Sixers&#821=
7; owners, private equity people themselves, brought in an unconventional s=
avior to shake things up: Hinkie. </p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size=
: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Hinkie&#8217;s approach in P=
hiladelphia was as unconventional as his background. <a href=3D"https://ema=
il.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFUMtuhDAM_BpyA-UBLBxy6KW_gRwwS7QhQYlTRL--WfZQyZqRb=
